\begin_layout Subsubsection
Vertical drift chambers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The vertical drift chambers (VDC) were used to measure the position and
 angle of incidence electrons at the spectrometer focal plane at a level
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm125\ \mbox{\mu m}$
\end_inset

 and 0.5 mrad, respectively 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "hallvdc"

\end_inset

.
 The diagram of the VDC is shown in figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:vdc"

\end_inset

 
