\begin_layout Standard
In g2p setting, the strong transverse target field makes the optics study
 more challenging.
 To deal with this target field, the reconstruction process is separated
 into two parts.
 The first part, containing the septum magnet and HRS, is assumed to be
 represented by the matrix with no target field which has been described
 above.
 Unfortunately, the configuration changes during the experiment because
 of the broken septum magnet, which requires the matrix elements to be re-calibr
ated.
 The simulation package mentioned above is used to calculate the reference
 angles of the fits for the recalibration.
 The second part, the target field region, is treated only with a ray-tracing
 method.
 The same simulation package is also used here to calculate the trajectory
 of the scattered electrons.
 
